{
  "stem": "22047.1",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He's way down there, and there's 500 of us, and he doesn't give a-- a hoot whether we learn or not.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I had a hard time in my first semester at UCLA.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And then I went in the service.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So I went in and started UCLA in-- in '42 and went into the service in early '43, so I didn't really finish my first year, although I got credit for it.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I didn't resume my college education until after the war.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I came back in '46 and went back to UCLA.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I still had a hard time because I had forgotten how to study.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I had a-- a counselor that I went to.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I told him that I was having a hard time studying.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And he-- he asked me, well, how do-- how do you do it?",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "How do you study?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I said, well, I-- I try to-- I read the textbooks, and then I try to remember what I read.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And he said, well, you know, what you really need to do is-- is read through and make notes, and then read it again, and then read it again for total context.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And ever after that, I-- I was OK with my studies.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "As a matter of fact, I did quite well at UCLA, where I graduated in 1950.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, I was-- I was Presbyterian.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Previous to that, I was sort of Christian Science, because my mother, she-- she became kind of chronically ill in her late '40s, and so we went to the Christian Science Church, which I didn't like very much.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And then I went to-- after that, she-- she left it also-- and I went and became a Presbyterian, and I'm now a Methodist.",
      "word_count": 24
    }
  ],
